In the same week that a family signed a 20-year lease to live on St Bees Island, one woman was so desperate to get off the private oasis that her friends made a huge SOS sign in the sand.

The 62-year-old woman fell out of a coconut tree on Thursday and had to be airlifted off the island with spinal injuries after landing on a rock.

Her friends made the SOS sign along with a cross and and arrow to help rescue choppers easily locate them on the island just off the coast of Mackay, north Queensland.

