The RACQ-CQ was so impressed with the forethought of the group that they were praised on Twitter.

‘Landing spot on #StBeesIsland made much easier to find by a big SOS in the sand. 2nd time this has helped this year!’.

In April, five people left stranded after their boat broke anchor 30km's north-east of Mackay were also rescued after emergency crews spotted their SOS message written on a sandbank.

Meanwhile, the new leaseholders of paradise will be the sole occupants of St Bees Island, which features three sea shanty-style cottages, a 100,000-litre water supply, a power generator and lots of coconut trees.

'There's not a lot to it, it's quite simple,' Mackay and Marina Real Estate licensee Kim Griffiths told Daily Mail Australia.

